which is supposed

00:17:53.740 --> 00:17:55.032 align:middle line:90%
to be throughout the universes.

00:17:55.032 --> 00:17:56.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Exactly, humanoid.

00:17:56.830 --> 00:17:57.630 align:middle line:90%
But they were big.

00:17:57.630 --> 00:17:58.805 align:middle line:90%
They were large.

00:17:58.805 --> 00:18:00.680 align:middle line:84%
And when I looked back
at the family history,

00:18:00.680 --> 00:18:03.140 align:middle line:90%
I keep seeing architects.

00:18:03.140 --> 00:18:07.640 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather, an
architect; my aunt

00:18:07.640 --> 00:18:10.670 align:middle line:84%
who unforeseen passed away as
well, her son and daughter--

00:18:10.670 --> 00:18:11.690 align:middle line:90%
both architects.

00:18:11.690 --> 00:18:13.910 align:middle line:84%
I'm going, wow, this
is really interesting.

00:18:13.910 --> 00:18:15.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, and they're not
even going to school

00:18:15.830 --> 00:18:17.600 align:middle line:90%
for just particularly that.

00:18:17.600 --> 00:18:19.843 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather, only an
eighth-grade education,

00:18:19.843 --> 00:18:21.260 align:middle line:84%
becomes one of the
top architects.

00:18:21.260 --> 00:18:23.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, let's talk
about what happened to his life

00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:24.410 align:middle line:90%
and how that even happened.

00:18:24.410 --> 00:18:26.237 align:middle line:84%
How did anyone even
know about this man?

00:18:26.237 --> 00:18:27.320 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: It's incredible.

00:18:27.320 --> 00:18:29.020 align:middle line:84%
I really don't have
the slightest clue.

00:18:29.020 --> 00:18:31.015 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'm working
on trying to do

00:18:31.015 --> 00:18:33.140 align:middle line:84%
a little documentary about
this because it's really

00:18:33.140 --> 00:18:34.400 align:middle line:90%
an amazing story.

00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:38.180 align:middle line:84%
And my cousin, who's watching
now, she's like the caregiver

00:18:38.180 --> 00:18:40.880 align:middle line:84%
for my grandmother
right now, my nana,

00:18:40.880 --> 00:18:42.625 align:middle line:84%
she's digging through
all the old photos

00:18:42.625 --> 00:18:44.000 align:middle line:84%
to bring up the
photos that I can

00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:45.310 align:middle line:90%
put in a little mini series.

00:18:45.310 --> 00:18:47.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's tell
about his life-- who he was.

00:18:47.900 --> 00:18:50.375 align:middle line:84%
And we know he was
married your grandma,

00:18:50.375 --> 00:18:52.270 align:middle line:90%
and he was from St. Thomas.

00:18:52.270 --> 00:18:54.442 align:middle line:84%
OK, let's find
out what happened.

00:18:54.442 --> 00:18:56.900 align:middle line:84%
Because as you said, he only
had an eighth-grade education.

00:18:56.900 --> 00:18:58.410 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Yeah, he started
out as a fisherman.

00:18:58.410 --> 00:18:59.900 align:middle line:90%
