00:21:26.490 --> 00:21:27.760 align:middle line:90%
in their perceptions of life?

00:21:27.760 --> 00:21:28.560 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:21:28.560 --> 00:21:29.810 align:middle line:90%
I have an aunt--

00:21:29.810 --> 00:21:33.770 align:middle line:84%
now she was really amazing
because she had the capability

00:21:33.770 --> 00:21:36.420 align:middle line:90%
of seeing way in the future.

00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:39.862 align:middle line:84%
Now my dad was driving for this
company called Handi-Van, which

00:21:39.862 --> 00:21:41.570 align:middle line:84%
I think might be still
in business today,

00:21:41.570 --> 00:21:43.970 align:middle line:84%
so it's well documented
this situation.

00:21:43.970 --> 00:21:46.130 align:middle line:84%
He was driving
elderly people around.

00:21:46.130 --> 00:21:49.040 align:middle line:84%
My aunt contacted
us and she said--

00:21:49.040 --> 00:21:50.390 align:middle line:90%
her name was Aunt Doris--

00:21:50.390 --> 00:21:52.730 align:middle line:84%
she said, your father--
she told my mom,

00:21:52.730 --> 00:21:54.980 align:middle line:84%
your husband's going to be
in a very bad car accident.

00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:57.440 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's going
to die, but his life

00:21:57.440 --> 00:21:58.880 align:middle line:84%
is going to be
restored, but he'll

00:21:58.880 --> 00:22:00.590 align:middle line:90%
be in the hospital for a while.

00:22:00.590 --> 00:22:01.610 align:middle line:90%
And my mom went crazy.

00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:03.110 align:middle line:84%
Don't call me telling
me this stuff.

00:22:03.110 --> 00:22:04.010 align:middle line:90%
This is scary stuff.

00:22:04.010 --> 00:22:05.600 align:middle line:90%
Blah, blah, blah.

00:22:05.600 --> 00:22:07.520 align:middle line:84%
Three weeks later,
a tractor trailer

00:22:07.520 --> 00:22:10.820 align:middle line:84%
