Like I said, I'm seeing 50
different paths of conversation

00:22:55.100 --> 00:22:56.000 align:middle line:90%
to take right now.

00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:58.250 align:middle line:84%
OK, so let's just stay
on that one for a minute

00:22:58.250 --> 00:23:01.770 align:middle line:84%
before we go back
to some other stuff.

00:23:01.770 --> 00:23:05.420 align:middle line:84%
After Aunt Doris started
being respected by the family

00:23:05.420 --> 00:23:08.960 align:middle line:84%
and she'd tell them things,
did they alter their behavior

00:23:08.960 --> 00:23:10.390 align:middle line:90%
and alter the outcomes?

00:23:10.390 --> 00:23:13.430 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: People became much
more aware and much more

00:23:13.430 --> 00:23:15.990 align:middle line:84%
cautious of situations to try
to figure out when things were

00:23:15.990 --> 00:23:16.790 align:middle line:90%
going--

00:23:16.790 --> 00:23:18.170 align:middle line:84%
to have better intuition
about when things

00:23:18.170 --> 00:23:19.420 align:middle line:90%
were going to happen or occur.

00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:21.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did they actually
avoid those things happening?

00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:23.150 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Some people
avoided some of the things,

00:23:23.150 --> 00:23:24.680 align:middle line:90%
and some people weren't able to.

00:23:24.680 --> 00:23:26.760 align:middle line:10%
So I guess it--

00:23:26.760 --> 00:23:29.790 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: I mean, that's, to
me, interesting, of course.

00:23:29.790 --> 00:23:33.500 align:middle line:10%
Because as the saying goes,
it is written, darling,

00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:37.820 align:middle line:10%
my ballet guru teacher used to
tell me, it is written darling.

00:23:37.820 --> 00:23:42.653 align:middle line:10%
And so you wonder in something
like that if-- your father,

00:23:42.653 --> 00:23:45.070 align:middle line:10%
if he was driving for a living,
he couldn't avoid driving.

00:23:45.070 --> 00:23:45.870 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: Right.

00:23:45.870 --> 00:23:49.478 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: So it sounded like
this was destined to occur

00:23:49.478 --> 00:23:51.020 align:middle line:10%
or she would not
have been seeing it.

00:23:51.020 --> 00:23:54.930 align:middle line:84%
So in some timeline, some
reality, it had occurred.

00:23:54.930 --> 00:23:56.810 align:middle line:84%
But as you say,
some of the events

00:23:56.810 --> 00:24:00.170 align:middle line:84%
were actually avoided by simply
increasing one's awareness.

00:24:00.170 --> 00:24:01.655 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Right
example, let's say

00:24:01.655 --> 00:24:04.280 align:middle line:84%
he decided, well, I'm not going
to drive for Handi-Van anymore.

00:24:04.280 --> 00:24:06.820 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to stop
driving for this company.

00:24:06.820 --> 00:24:09.320 align:middle line:84%
And let's say he decided to
go into mechanic work, which

00:24:09.320 --> 00:24:11.468 align:middle line:90%
is what he did before.

00:24:11.468 --> 00:24:13.010 align:middle line:84%
He could have averted
that situation.

00:24:13.010 --> 00:24:16.510 align:middle line:84%
But how do you know for sure
this is really going to happen?

00:24:16.510 --> 00:24:17.690 align:middle line:90%
I need this money.

00:24:17.690 --> 00:24:19.730 align:middle line:84%
I have to pay my bills
and take care of my kids.

00:24:19.730 --> 00:24:21.813 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you don't
know where-- in this case,

00:24:21.813 --> 00:24:22.615 align:middle line:90%
she was very clear.

00:24:22.615 --> 00:24:23.990 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they
have those things,

00:24:23.990 --> 00:24:25.160 align:middle line:90%
but they're not as specific.

00:24:25.160 --> 00:24:29.750 align:middle line:10%
It's like, one dream, I rolled
in the side of a-- it almost

00:24:29.750 --> 00:24:33.130 align:middle line:10%
looked like a Costco, but it was
all white with white walls that

00:24:33.130 --> 00:24:35.270 align:middle line:10%
rolled up and my
white car inside,

00:24:35.270 --> 00:24:37.610 align:middle line:10%
and the radio came on
on its own it said,

00:24:37.610 --> 00:24:40.040 align:middle line:10%
we know you've been through
a lot of loss and pain,

00:24:40.040 --> 00:24:41.060 align:middle line:10%
but there's more coming.

00:24:41.060 --> 00:24:42.757 align:middle line:10%
Know we're with you.

00:24:42.757 --> 00:24:44.840 align:middle line:84%
So my father and my son
were going in a helicopter

00:24:44.840 --> 00:24:46.880 align:middle line:90%
the next day over Yosemite.

00:24:46.880 --> 00:24:48.320 align:middle line:90%
So I tried to interfere.

00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:49.490 align:middle line:90%
I did interfere.

00:24:49.490 --> 00:24:51.950 align:middle line:84%
I said, I can't
let my son go, Dad.

00:24:51.950 --> 00:24:54.720 align:middle line:84%
You can go if you want,
but I can't let my son go.

00:24:54.720 --> 00:24:55.520 align:middle line:90%
It was fine.

00:24:55.520 --> 00:24:58.707 align:middle line:10%
But three days later, my mentor,
the woman I mentioned, died.

00:24:58.707 --> 00:24:59.790 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: Oh, my goodness.

00:24:59.790 --> 00:25:01.130 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah, she died.

00:25:01.130 --> 00:25:04.040 align:middle line:10%
And she was a big
person, and personality,

00:25:04.040 --> 00:25:06.200 align:middle line:10%
and an influence in my life.

00:25:06.200 --> 00:25:08.390 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't know
where it was coming from.

00:25:08.390 --> 00:25:12.230 align:middle line:84%
And so you can't necessarily--
it is written to an extent

00:25:12.230 --> 00:25:14.960 align:middle line:84%
but, again, when
people listened,

00:25:14.960 --> 00:25:17.440 align:middle line:84%
they were able to
avoid some of it.

00:25:17.440 --> 00:25:18.770 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Right.

00:25:18.770 --> 00:25:19.610 align:middle line:90%
It's a tricky thing.

00:25:19.610 --> 00:25:20.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's a tricky thing.

00:25:20.860 --> 00:25:21.660 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:25:21.660 --> 00:25:26.510 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: OK, so your
grandfather had then done this.

00:25:26.510 --> 00:25:28.760 align:middle line:84%
He had worked with
this German team

00:25:28.760 --> 00:25:30.690 align:middle line:90%
on the restoration and such.

00:25:30.690 --> 00:25:35.030 align:middle line:10%
Now continue your own
family story then into you

00:25:35.030 --> 00:25:38.330 align:middle line:10%
because this whole notion
that you remember your life

00:25:38.330 --> 00:25:41.060 align:middle line:10%
from birth, you came
in fully awake aware,

00:25:41.060 --> 00:25:42.375 align:middle line:10%
and you remember from birth.

00:25:42.375 --> 00:25:45.410 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: I was a
10.5 pound baby--

00:25:45.410 --> 00:25:47.080 align:middle line:10%
10 pounds, 5 ounces.

00:25:47.080 --> 00:25:48.540 align:middle line:10%
I was a 10-month baby as well.

00:25:48.540 --> 00:25:49.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:25:49.400 --> 00:25:50.840 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: I was 10, 10, 5.

00:25:50.840 --> 00:25:53.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:25:53.020 --> 00:25:55.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: My mom,
everybody jokes,

00:25:55.160 --> 00:25:56.660 align:middle line:84%
said I split her
from front to back.

00:25:56.660 --> 00:25:58.190 align:middle line:84%
She actually didn't
have a C-section.

00:25:58.190 --> 00:25:58.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:25:58.990 --> 00:25:59.200 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:25:59.200 --> 00:25:59.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Ow.

00:25:59.790 --> 00:26:00.748 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah, I know.

00:26:00.748 --> 00:26:03.200 align:middle line:84%
So for whatever reason,
according to my family,

00:26:03.200 --> 00:26:04.880 align:middle line:84%
I was in the hospital
for three weeks.

00:26:04.880 --> 00:26:05.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Why?

00:26:05.680 --> 00:26:07.055 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: They
had to keep trying

00:26:07.055 --> 00:26:08.630 align:middle line:10%
to transfuse me
and everything else

00:26:08.630 --> 00:26:11.750 align:middle line:10%
because I was having
some kind of rejection.

00:26:11.750 --> 00:26:13.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's part of
the Rh negative issue?

00:26:13.630 --> 00:26:15.130 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: That's
what my cousin told

00:26:15.130 --> 00:26:16.830 align:middle line:90%
me, who was closest to my mom.

00:26:16.830 --> 00:26:18.320 align:middle line:90%
She's my older cousin.

00:26:18.320 --> 00:26:19.880 align:middle line:84%
And I was like,
wow, I gotta really

00:26:19.880 --> 00:26:21.463 align:middle line:84%
get a lot more
information about this.

00:26:21.463 --> 00:26:23.580 align:middle line:84%
My mom never told
me about that part.

00:26:23.580 --> 00:26:25.610 align:middle line:84%
And this I found out when,
unfortunately, my dad

00:26:25.610 --> 00:26:28.890 align:middle line:84%
passed away recently after I
talked to you the last time,

00:26:28.890 --> 00:26:29.690 align:middle line:90%
after I--

00:26:29.690 --> 00:26:30.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, he did?

00:26:30.620 --> 00:26:30.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:26:30.830 --> 00:26:32.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Were you
expecting that at the time?

00:26:32.360 --> 00:26:32.980 align:middle line:90%
Did you know?

00:26:32.980 --> 00:26:33.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: No.

00:26:33.350 --> 00:26:34.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What happened?

00:26:34.350 --> 00:26:38.090 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: He, unfortunately,
had a police brutality incident

00:26:38.090 --> 00:26:40.760 align:middle line:84%
about four years ago,
where they broke his back

00:26:40.760 --> 00:26:43.220 align:middle line:84%
and gave him a
double concussion.

00:26:43.220 --> 00:26:44.600 align:middle line:90%
Somebody made a 9-1-1 call.

00:26:44.600 --> 00:26:47.090 align:middle line:84%
He was at a concert sitting
in the front row in a suit

00:26:47.090 --> 00:26:48.260 align:middle line:90%
that I bought him.

00:26:48.260 --> 00:26:51.358 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, they
didn't like his color,

00:26:51.358 --> 00:26:53.900 align:middle line:84%
so they called the cops and said
this guy just stole the seat

00:26:53.900 --> 00:26:55.220 align:middle line:90%
in the front row, supposedly.

00:26:55.220 --> 00:26:56.465 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm so sorry.

00:26:56.465 --> 00:26:58.850 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: And four cops came
in and beat him up in front

00:26:58.850 --> 00:27:01.230 align:middle line:84%
of the whole concert, on all
the tapes, all the cameras--

00:27:01.230 --> 00:27:02.210 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is in
the last two months?

00:27:02.210 --> 00:27:04.252 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: No, they did
this four years ago years.

00:27:04.252 --> 00:27:06.860 align:middle line:84%
But the concussion,
it messed his mind up.

00:27:06.860 --> 00:27:07.985 align:middle line:90%
He started losing his mind.

00:27:07.985 --> 00:27:10.277 align:middle line:84%
Right after that, he started
forgetting so many things,

00:27:10.277 --> 00:27:11.090 align:middle line:90%
forgetting to eat.

00:27:11.090 --> 00:27:12.620 align:middle line:90%
He was already 74 at that time.

00:27:12.620 --> 00:27:15.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so he had the
concussion at that time.

00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.425 align:middle line:84%
What happened in the
last couple months?

00:27:17.425 --> 00:27:19.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Eating was
the biggest thing.

00:27:19.050 --> 00:27:20.330 align:middle line:90%
He keeps forgetting to eat.

00:27:20.330 --> 00:27:21.740 align:middle line:84%
Even if you give
him food and you

00:27:21.740 --> 00:27:23.658 align:middle line:84%
try to force feed it to
him, if you walk away,

00:27:23.658 --> 00:27:24.950 align:middle line:90%
he'll forget you gave him food.

00:27:24.950 --> 00:27:25.867 align:middle line:90%
He won't eat anything.

00:27:25.867 --> 00:27:28.640 align:middle line:84%
So he started getting
very malnourished.

00:27:28.640 --> 00:27:31.287 align:middle line:84%
Went to the hospital to look
at that-- also, his back.

00:27:31.287 --> 00:27:32.120 align:middle line:90%
They broke his back.

00:27:32.120 --> 00:27:33.800 align:middle line:84%
It started hurting
him really bad.

00:27:33.800 --> 00:27:34.850 align:middle line:90%
They checked him in.

00:27:34.850 --> 00:27:36.267 align:middle line:84%
And they said,
we're going to have

00:27:36.267 --> 00:27:39.080 align:middle line:84%
to try to figure out what
we can do for your back.

00:27:39.080 --> 00:27:42.770 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, my dad had
turned to alcohol and pain

00:27:42.770 --> 00:27:44.210 align:middle line:90%
medicine.

00:27:44.210 --> 00:27:48.090 align:middle line:84%
And he was on so much of
that when they took him

00:27:48.090 --> 00:27:49.700 align:middle line:84%
in to the hospital
and didn't give him

00:27:49.700 --> 00:27:54.260 align:middle line:84%
that, replacement of that,
he went through withdrawals.

00:27:54.260 --> 00:27:56.690 align:middle line:84%
And that led him into a
seizure, and that turned

00:27:56.690 --> 00:27:59.307 align:middle line:90%
into 100 seizures in two days.

00:27:59.307 --> 00:28:00.890 align:middle line:84%
Even on the highest
seizure medication

00:28:00.890 --> 00:28:05.100 align:middle line:84%
they couldn't stop them, and
the seizures erased his mind.

00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:07.287 align:middle line:90%
And then he became brain dead.

00:28:07.287 --> 00:28:08.660 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:28:08.660 --> 00:28:09.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Gosh.

00:28:09.950 --> 00:28:11.780 align:middle line:90%
Well, I mean, I'm sorry.

00:28:11.780 --> 00:28:13.400 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Thank you.

00:28:13.400 --> 00:28:16.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you had a
complex relationship with him.

00:28:16.490 --> 00:28:17.955 align:middle line:90%
He had a rough go of it himself?

00:28:17.955 --> 00:28:20.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Yeah, he was
really a depressed person.

00:28:20.840 --> 00:28:22.970 align:middle line:84%
His mom died when
he was 16, his dad

00:28:22.970 --> 00:28:25.100 align:middle line:84%
when he was just a small
boy, left the house, never

00:28:25.100 --> 00:28:26.128 align:middle line:90%
came back.

00:28:26.128 --> 00:28:27.920 align:middle line:84%
And so he was depressed
miles of this life.

00:28:27.920 --> 00:28:29.337 align:middle line:84%
And then I look
back, and I see he

00:28:29.337 --> 00:28:30.668 align:middle line:90%
was mentally ill and depressed.

00:28:30.668 --> 00:28:32.210 align:middle line:84%
So I started a
foundation in his name

00:28:32.210 --> 00:28:35.570 align:middle line:84%
called the Carson Foundation
for Addiction and Depression.

00:28:35.570 --> 00:28:38.472 align:middle line:10%
And I located a very
good place in Florida

00:28:38.472 --> 00:28:40.430 align:middle line:10%
that can take people from
anywhere in the world

00:28:40.430 --> 00:28:43.580 align:middle line:10%
and help treat them
with that sickness--

00:28:43.580 --> 00:28:48.605 align:middle line:10%
any kind of addiction and
any kind of depression.

00:28:48.605 --> 00:28:50.837 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did you know
he was in the hospital

00:28:50.837 --> 00:28:51.920 align:middle line:90%
or did you find out after?

00:28:51.920 --> 00:28:52.550 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: I found out after.

00:28:52.550 --> 00:28:54.330 align:middle line:84%
He had a neighbor take
him to the hospital.

00:28:54.330 --> 00:28:55.190 align:middle line:90%
His back was hurting too much.

00:28:55.190 --> 00:28:56.520 align:middle line:90%
He walked into the hospital.

00:28:56.520 --> 00:28:57.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:28:57.320 --> 00:28:58.130 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: And by
the time I found out

00:28:58.130 --> 00:29:00.470 align:middle line:84%
he was in the hospital,
it was two days later.

00:29:00.470 --> 00:29:02.250 align:middle line:90%
He was already in a coma.

00:29:02.250 --> 00:29:04.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So did you have
a chance, on some level,

00:29:04.880 --> 00:29:08.360 align:middle line:84%
on some plane, to be
able to kind of reconcile

00:29:08.360 --> 00:29:09.620 align:middle line:90%
and say goodbye?

00:29:09.620 --> 00:29:11.540 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Well,
when I went up there

00:29:11.540 --> 00:29:13.877 align:middle line:84%
and while he was
out of it really,

00:29:13.877 --> 00:29:15.460 align:middle line:84%
I just spent some
time with him there.

00:29:15.460 --> 00:29:17.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Because they're there.

00:29:17.060 --> 00:29:17.360 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:29:17.360 --> 00:29:19.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I did that with
my mom who was in a coma.

00:29:19.460 --> 00:29:20.150 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Absolutely.

00:29:20.150 --> 00:29:21.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're
hearing everything.

00:29:21.110 --> 00:29:22.850 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Yeah, ironically,
it was in the same hospital

00:29:22.850 --> 00:29:23.660 align:middle line:90%
that my mom died.

00:29:23.660 --> 00:29:25.860 align:middle line:84%
And he was in the room
directly next to the room

00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:26.660 align:middle line:90%
that she died in--

00:29:26.660 --> 00:29:27.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:29:27.320 --> 00:29:28.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: --in the same ICU.

00:29:28.350 --> 00:29:29.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So where
were you kind of--

00:29:29.930 --> 00:29:32.540 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: I was just trying to
communicate with him mentally

00:29:32.540 --> 00:29:35.090 align:middle line:84%
and just let him know I love
him, rubbing him on his head,

00:29:35.090 --> 00:29:37.632 align:middle line:84%
kissing him on his head, letting
him know that it's OK to go.

00:29:37.632 --> 00:29:38.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Nice.

00:29:38.910 --> 00:29:42.650 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: It's time for
you to just be free,

00:29:42.650 --> 00:29:43.572 align:middle line:90%
shed this mortal coil.

00:29:43.572 --> 00:29:45.530 align:middle line:84%
It's time for you to just
be free and be happy.

00:29:45.530 --> 00:29:46.035 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:46.035 --> 00:29:47.452 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: He
suffered long enough.

00:29:47.452 --> 00:29:49.460 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
yeah, and I know it

00:29:49.460 --> 00:29:52.167 align:middle line:10%
created some trouble
in his relationships

00:29:52.167 --> 00:29:53.000 align:middle line:10%
with everybody else.

00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:54.210 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Yeah, including
with me as well.

00:29:54.210 --> 00:29:55.300 align:middle line:90%
It was tough at times.

00:29:55.300 --> 00:29:56.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:56.100 --> 00:29:57.850 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: So I had to
move out when I was.

00:29:57.850 --> 00:30:00.120 align:middle line:84%
16 It was just just too much
dealing with the problems

00:30:00.120 --> 00:30:00.920 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:30:00.920 --> 00:30:01.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Right,
that kind of pain.

00:30:01.570 --> 00:30:02.030 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Mm-hm.

00:30:02.030 --> 00:30:03.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But still,
that those things still

00:30:03.500 --> 00:30:05.570 align:middle line:84%
exist in this world gets
tears behind my eyes

00:30:05.570 --> 00:30:08.270 align:middle line:84%
because we should be
less barbaric than that

00:30:08.270 --> 00:30:09.080 align:middle line:90%
by now, right?

00:30:09.080 --> 00:30:09.920 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Right, right.

00:30:09.920 --> 00:30:11.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you've had to
deal with stuff in your life?

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:12.180 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:30:12.180 --> 00:30:12.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right?

00:30:12.690 --> 00:30:13.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:30:13.490 --> 00:30:18.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So now, basically,
you're on top of it.

00:30:18.050 --> 00:30:18.910 align:middle line:90%
You've come out OK.

00:30:18.910 --> 00:30:19.710 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:30:19.710 --> 00:30:22.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did you use those
challenges of your youth--

00:30:22.190 --> 00:30:25.490 align:middle line:84%
this is just kind of
some psychology here--

00:30:25.490 --> 00:30:27.500 align:middle line:84%
did they drive you
in a special way?

00:30:27.500 --> 00:30:30.770 align:middle line:84%
And I asked that
for obvious reasons,

00:30:30.770 --> 00:30:35.000 align:middle line:84%
but also there was a trailer
for a film recently I saw.

00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:38.060 align:middle line:90%
The name of it as "Waves."

00:30:38.060 --> 00:30:40.260 align:middle line:84%
At this moment--
it's coming out soon.

00:30:40.260 --> 00:30:44.750 align:middle line:84%
And the African-American
man in it was saying,

00:30:44.750 --> 00:30:45.800 align:middle line:90%
you don't understand.

00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:47.825 align:middle line:90%
We can't afford to be average.

00:30:47.825 --> 00:30:49.040 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah, that's true.

00:30:49.040 --> 00:30:50.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We have to try harder.

00:30:50.600 --> 00:30:52.160 align:middle line:90%
We can't afford average.

00:30:52.160 --> 00:30:53.060 align:middle line:90%
They can, we can't.

00:30:53.060 --> 00:30:53.390 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:30:53.390 --> 00:30:55.265 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: So talk about
that for a moment,

00:30:55.265 --> 00:30:56.390 align:middle line:10%
just from your perspective.

00:30:56.390 --> 00:30:59.120 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Well, I'll
give you an example.

00:30:59.120 --> 00:31:03.250 align:middle line:84%
The first time I came to Gaia,
which was 2016, to record--

00:31:03.250 --> 00:31:05.873 align:middle line:84%
I came to just meet,
actually, with the owner.

00:31:05.873 --> 00:31:07.790 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know I was
going to be recording.

00:31:07.790 --> 00:31:10.220 align:middle line:84%
But I came in a
three-piece suit,

00:31:10.220 --> 00:31:12.710 align:middle line:84%
and then they said,
you know, Melissa Tittl

00:31:12.710 --> 00:31:16.130 align:middle line:84%
would like to ask you a
few questions about space.

00:31:16.130 --> 00:31:19.008 align:middle line:84%
So next thing I know, I'm doing
a whole interview on a camera.

00:31:19.008 --> 00:31:21.050 align:middle line:84%
And they were like, next
time you come here, just

00:31:21.050 --> 00:31:21.850 align:middle line:90%
put on a t-shirt.

00:31:21.850 --> 00:31:23.180 align:middle line:90%
You can be comfortable.

00:31:23.180 --> 00:31:24.540 align:middle line:90%
I was like, no.

00:31:24.540 --> 00:31:26.748 align:middle line:84%
There's no way in the world
I'm going to come in here

00:31:26.748 --> 00:31:29.040 align:middle line:84%
with a t-shirt and a cap
on and being on TV talking

00:31:29.040 --> 00:31:31.137 align:middle line:84%
about these kind of
controversial topics

00:31:31.137 --> 00:31:33.220 align:middle line:84%
and think people are going
to actually believe me.

00:31:33.220 --> 00:31:35.130 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah, you're not gonna
do the Michael Moore thing.

00:31:35.130 --> 00:31:36.242 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: No, I can't--

00:31:36.242 --> 00:31:37.700 align:middle line:84%
some people can
get away with that.

00:31:37.700 --> 00:31:40.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm on shows where I'm
in a three-piece suit,

00:31:40.340 --> 00:31:42.500 align:middle line:84%
and the next guy who's
doing his little bit,

00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:44.218 align:middle line:84%
he's got a baseball
cap on and t-shirt.

00:31:44.218 --> 00:31:46.010 align:middle line:84%
And people will believe
him, but that's OK.

00:31:46.010 --> 00:31:49.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you feel that
that extra level of-- you

00:31:49.160 --> 00:31:52.430 align:middle line:84%
have to go the extra mile
to receive the credibility,

00:31:52.430 --> 00:31:55.120 align:middle line:84%
as brilliant as you are
and as much as you've done,

00:31:55.120 --> 00:31:57.950 align:middle line:84%
you still feel you still have
to create the appearance that

00:31:57.950 --> 00:32:01.880 align:middle line:84%
will bring forth respectability
on the first encounter?

00:32:01.880 --> 00:32:04.450 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Absolutely,
there's no doubt about it.

00:32:04.450 --> 00:32:06.290 align:middle line:84%
And I live my life
that way, always

00:32:06.290 --> 00:32:08.300 align:middle line:90%
trying to excel and be above.

00:32:08.300 --> 00:32:10.370 align:middle line:84%
I remember I came home
crying one day from school

00:32:10.370 --> 00:32:12.063 align:middle line:90%
because I had an A-minus.

00:32:12.063 --> 00:32:13.730 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was going
to get in trouble.

00:32:13.730 --> 00:32:17.020 align:middle line:84%
I had never had anything
less than an A or an A-plus.

00:32:17.020 --> 00:32:19.450 align:middle line:84%
And my mom, of course,
she laughed at me,

00:32:19.450 --> 00:32:22.100 align:middle line:84%
but I literally
thought that was bad.

00:32:22.100 --> 00:32:24.695 align:middle line:84%
I was always seeking to
overachieve because I wanted

00:32:24.695 --> 00:32:26.570 align:middle line:84%
that level of respect,
and I understood early

00:32:26.570 --> 00:32:30.410 align:middle line:84%
on that because of my situation,
and my condition, and my race,

00:32:30.410 --> 00:32:34.187 align:middle line:84%
you have to do a little bit
more sometimes to get noticed.

00:32:34.187 --> 00:32:36.020 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't just just
from the History Channel

00:32:36.020 --> 00:32:37.280 align:middle line:90%
that I got noticed.

00:32:37.280 --> 00:32:39.340 align:middle line:10%
Like, to get into
lecturing, I literally

00:32:39.340 --> 00:32:42.410 align:middle line:10%
begged the Conscious Life
Expo, contacting the--

00:32:42.410 --> 00:32:45.013 align:middle line:10%
I bugged them for three
years each to get on.

00:32:45.013 --> 00:32:46.680 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah, there
aren't many people

00:32:46.680 --> 00:32:47.840 align:middle line:10%
of color lecturing there.

00:32:47.840 --> 00:32:49.140 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: No, not at all.

00:32:49.140 --> 00:32:50.786 align:middle line:10%
And finally, after the
third year, both of them,

00:32:50.786 --> 00:32:52.703 align:middle line:10%
after three years of
bugging them and begging,

00:32:52.703 --> 00:32:54.290 align:middle line:10%
they finally gave me a chance.

00:32:54.290 --> 00:32:56.070 align:middle line:84%
And when I went in there, I
made sure I knocked it out

00:32:56.070 --> 00:32:56.870 align:middle line:90%
of the park.

00:32:56.870 --> 00:32:59.292 align:middle line:90%


00:32:59.292 --> 00:33:05.365 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so let's
go ahead and continue on.

00:33:05.365 --> 00:33:06.990 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to go back
for a moment to let

00:33:06.990 --> 00:33:10.830 align:middle line:84%
living life as a conscious
person from day one.

00:33:10.830 --> 00:33:13.360 align:middle line:84%
I mean, obviously, you
didn't know it any other way.

00:33:13.360 --> 00:33:16.135 align:middle line:84%
So how did you operate--
how did it work for you?

00:33:16.135 --> 00:33:17.760 align:middle line:84%
Because I've always
wondered about this

00:33:17.760 --> 00:33:20.010 align:middle line:84%
with conscious
babies, the ones who

00:33:20.010 --> 00:33:22.500 align:middle line:90%
come in with full awareness.

00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:26.250 align:middle line:84%
How does it work to have your
full awareness and your memory

00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:28.798 align:middle line:84%
and not be able to do anything
with it in the little vehicle?

00:33:28.798 --> 00:33:30.090 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: It's kind of bizarre.

00:33:30.090 --> 00:33:34.170 align:middle line:84%
Like, I wasn't fully aware
of any past memories,

00:33:34.170 --> 00:33:35.940 align:middle line:84%
but I did have a
good understanding

00:33:35.940 --> 00:33:38.190 align:middle line:84%
of exactly what was going
on, what people were saying.

00:33:38.190 --> 00:33:41.370 align:middle line:84%
And I really couldn't understand
until a little bit later how.

00:33:41.370 --> 00:33:43.350 align:middle line:84%
But early on, I just
knew-- like, for example,

00:33:43.350 --> 00:33:45.240 align:middle line:84%
my grandmother
put me on her lap.

00:33:45.240 --> 00:33:47.520 align:middle line:84%
Everybody came over because
it was my first day home--

00:33:47.520 --> 00:33:48.960 align:middle line:90%
I survived.

00:33:48.960 --> 00:33:50.820 align:middle line:84%
They're all around
the kitchen table,

00:33:50.820 --> 00:33:52.290 align:middle line:84%
and my grandmother
starts giving me

00:33:52.290 --> 00:33:55.710 align:middle line:84%
table food, which was bluefish,
not the whole chunk of fish,

00:33:55.710 --> 00:33:58.917 align:middle line:84%
but just sops of the juice
of the fish and everything.

00:33:58.917 --> 00:34:00.000 align:middle line:90%
And I remember that taste.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:01.065 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Kind of
like an initiation.

00:34:01.065 --> 00:34:02.100 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:34:02.100 --> 00:34:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And I remember it,
and it was so clear,

00:34:04.260 --> 00:34:06.780 align:middle line:84%
but nobody ever talked
about it after that.

00:34:06.780 --> 00:34:08.429 align:middle line:84%
And one day, we all
came together for,

00:34:08.429 --> 00:34:10.710 align:middle line:84%
I think it was Thanksgiving
or something, and I said,

00:34:10.710 --> 00:34:12.511 align:middle line:84%
you remember when you
put me on your lap

00:34:12.511 --> 00:34:14.969 align:middle line:84%
and gave me that blue fish,
that table food on my first day

00:34:14.969 --> 00:34:15.630 align:middle line:90%
home from the hospital?

00:34:15.630 --> 00:34:17.010 align:middle line:90%
You think hat was smart to do?

00:34:17.010 --> 00:34:18.989 align:middle line:90%
And everybody goes, what?

00:34:18.989 --> 00:34:20.460 align:middle line:90%
And everybody went crazy.

00:34:20.460 --> 00:34:21.260 align:middle line:90%
Like, how--

00:34:21.260 --> 00:34:22.770 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I remember.

00:34:22.770 --> 00:34:25.440 align:middle line:84%
I remember when I just came
back from Cambria Heights

00:34:25.440 --> 00:34:26.929 align:middle line:90%
two weeks ago.

00:34:26.929 --> 00:34:29.460 align:middle line:84%
And I went to go visit the old
house that we were living in,

00:34:29.460 --> 00:34:31.380 align:middle line:84%
because I was up there
doing a big lecture.

00:34:31.380 --> 00:34:35.417 align:middle line:84%
And I saw the air conditioner in
the front of the house, the box

00:34:35.417 --> 00:34:37.500 align:middle line:84%
air conditioner where my
mom would put the bubbles

00:34:37.500 --> 00:34:38.940 align:middle line:84%
when I was only 1
and 2 years old,

00:34:38.940 --> 00:34:40.190 align:middle line:90%
to fill the room with bubbles.

00:34:40.190 --> 00:34:41.610 align:middle line:90%
And all those things I remember.

00:34:41.610 --> 00:34:43.402 align:middle line:84%
I remember all the book
reports that I did.

00:34:43.402 --> 00:34:45.989 align:middle line:84%
My dad would make me do a
book report every single week

00:34:45.989 --> 00:34:46.830 align:middle line:90%
at that young age.

00:34:46.830 --> 00:34:48.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:34:48.210 --> 00:34:52.425 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: All the memories are
so vivid still, which is great.

00:34:52.425 --> 00:34:54.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, you're
the record keeper.

00:34:54.150 --> 00:34:55.980 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Yeah, my
recall is excellent.

00:34:55.980 --> 00:34:57.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, clearly.

00:34:57.580 --> 00:34:59.150 align:middle line:84%
And now what about
your own kids?

00:34:59.150 --> 00:35:00.840 align:middle line:90%
Now they grew up in privilege.

00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:02.510 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah, they did.

00:35:02.510 --> 00:35:03.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right?

00:35:03.310 --> 00:35:04.860 align:middle line:84%
So they didn't have
those struggles

00:35:04.860 --> 00:35:06.480 align:middle line:90%
to overcome that you had.

00:35:06.480 --> 00:35:09.078 align:middle line:84%
So what do you see
in the development

00:35:09.078 --> 00:35:10.120 align:middle line:90%
of your own children now?

00:35:10.120 --> 00:35:12.370 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: I let them kind
of each take their own path.

00:35:12.370 --> 00:35:14.490 align:middle line:84%
I didn't overwhelm
them with my ideals.

00:35:14.490 --> 00:35:17.280 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to see how they
all kind of developed.

00:35:17.280 --> 00:35:19.110 align:middle line:84%
I told them how I
felt, and I taught them

00:35:19.110 --> 00:35:23.070 align:middle line:84%
the way that I believe, but
I didn't punch it into them.

00:35:23.070 --> 00:35:25.800 align:middle line:84%
They had a very good life,
every single one of them.

00:35:25.800 --> 00:35:28.862 align:middle line:84%
And they all are a little bit
different, which is great.

00:35:28.862 --> 00:35:31.320 align:middle line:84%
Some of the kids are eating
meat, some kids don't eat meat,

00:35:31.320 --> 00:35:35.800 align:middle line:84%
some kids believe in
religion, and some don't.

00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:39.000 align:middle line:84%
But overall, I gave them a
very good incentive early on.

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:41.312 align:middle line:84%
I told them I wasn't going
to pay for any college

00:35:41.312 --> 00:35:42.770 align:middle line:84%
from the time they
were very small.

00:35:42.770 --> 00:35:43.800 align:middle line:84%
I said if you want
to go to college,

00:35:43.800 --> 00:35:46.133 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have to get
a scholarship for athletics,

00:35:46.133 --> 00:35:49.750 align:middle line:84%
or academics, or
fund it for yourself,

00:35:49.750 --> 00:35:51.250 align:middle line:90%
but I'm not paying for it.

00:35:51.250 --> 00:35:54.180 align:middle line:84%
And if you get straight
A's, you'll get $500.

00:35:54.180 --> 00:35:57.315 align:middle line:84%
If you get one B,
you get nothing.

00:35:57.315 --> 00:35:58.190 align:middle line:90%
So I instilled that--

00:35:58.190 --> 00:35:59.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You incentivize them.

00:35:59.070 --> 00:35:59.800 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: I incentivized them.

00:35:59.800 --> 00:36:01.883 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And how did they
rise to that challenge?

00:36:01.883 --> 00:36:04.740 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: They all became
Division I athletes.

00:36:04.740 --> 00:36:08.400 align:middle line:84%
All excelled-- state champion
in boxing, my youngest son.

00:36:08.400 --> 00:36:10.530 align:middle line:90%
I mean, they all--

00:36:10.530 --> 00:36:14.070 align:middle line:84%
University of North Carolina
Greensboro, Elon University.

00:36:14.070 --> 00:36:16.570 align:middle line:84%
My one daughter had
15 offers by the time

00:36:16.570 --> 00:36:19.200 align:middle line:84%
she got to the 10th
grade for scholarships.

00:36:19.200 --> 00:36:20.367 align:middle line:90%
They all excelled, you know?

00:36:20.367 --> 00:36:21.167 align:middle line:90%
All excelled.

00:36:21.167 --> 00:36:22.755 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Did they
ever resent you,

00:36:22.755 --> 00:36:24.550 align:middle line:10%
that you wouldn't
do that for them,

00:36:24.550 --> 00:36:27.450 align:middle line:10%
or did they know that you
created a sense of their own

00:36:27.450 --> 00:36:29.158 align:middle line:10%
excellence and help them--

00:36:29.158 --> 00:36:31.200 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: They loved it,
and they thank me for it

00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:32.140 align:middle line:10%
to this current day.

00:36:32.140 --> 00:36:33.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's so wonderful.

00:36:33.390 --> 00:36:35.307 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: There's so
many things in life now--

00:36:35.307 --> 00:36:37.173 align:middle line:90%
they're all grown up, obviously.

00:36:37.173 --> 00:36:38.715 align:middle line:84%
And when things come
at them, they're

00:36:38.715 --> 00:36:39.940 align:middle line:90%
just like, OK, whatever.

00:36:39.940 --> 00:36:41.140 align:middle line:90%
They're used to a work load.

00:36:41.140 --> 00:36:42.930 align:middle line:90%
They're used to being on time.

00:36:42.930 --> 00:36:44.490 align:middle line:90%
They're used to having so many--

00:36:44.490 --> 00:36:46.700 align:middle line:84%
multitasking and having
a lot of things to do,

00:36:46.700 --> 00:36:48.870 align:middle line:84%
so nothing really
overwhelms them.

00:36:48.870 --> 00:36:49.838 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:36:49.838 --> 00:36:51.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I want to see
a movie on your life,

00:36:51.630 --> 00:36:53.020 align:middle line:90%
but that will be down the road.

00:36:53.020 --> 00:36:54.600 align:middle line:84%
You're still a little too young
to have a movie on your life.

00:36:54.600 --> 00:36:55.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: I'll tell you
one more important thing.

00:36:55.230 --> 00:36:56.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, do.

00:36:56.030 --> 00:36:58.472 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: I never beat my kids,
and I never yelled at him.

00:36:58.472 --> 00:36:59.427 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Thank you.

00:36:59.427 --> 00:37:00.510 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah, important.

00:37:00.510 --> 00:37:02.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Nor did
I. I don't believe

00:37:02.010 --> 00:37:03.885 align:middle line:84%
that's the way you do
to another human being.

00:37:03.885 --> 00:37:05.080 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: You can't do it.

00:37:05.080 --> 00:37:05.340 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:37:05.340 --> 00:37:06.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All you do
is traumatize them.

00:37:06.810 --> 00:37:07.650 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: That's it.

00:37:07.650 --> 00:37:08.430 align:middle line:90%
You make them sick.

00:37:08.430 --> 00:37:09.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You make them sick.

00:37:09.210 --> 00:37:10.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: I went back
to my neighborhood,

00:37:10.230 --> 00:37:10.740 align:middle line:90%
and I'm telling you--

00:37:10.740 --> 00:37:12.823 align:middle line:84%
I'm getting a little
emotional because-- you know,

00:37:12.823 --> 00:37:14.330 align:middle line:90%
thinking about it--

00:37:14.330 --> 00:37:15.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's OK.

00:37:15.420 --> 00:37:17.845 align:middle line:90%
I hear you-- feel you.

00:37:17.845 --> 00:37:19.470 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: The people
there are hurting.

00:37:19.470 --> 00:37:20.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:37:20.270 --> 00:37:24.080 align:middle line:90%


00:37:24.080 --> 00:37:26.330 align:middle line:90%
They're traumatized every day.

00:37:26.330 --> 00:37:27.500 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:37:27.500 --> 00:37:30.357 align:middle line:84%
They're dead, locked up,
they're sick, they've got PTSD,

00:37:30.357 --> 00:37:31.190 align:middle line:90%
they became abusers.

00:37:31.190 --> 00:37:33.800 align:middle line:90%


00:37:33.800 --> 00:37:35.150 align:middle line:90%
It's horrible.

00:37:35.150 --> 00:37:37.776 align:middle line:90%
It's pretty bad.

00:37:37.776 --> 00:37:41.015 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: And they're tucked
away, and the media ignores--

00:37:41.015 --> 00:37:43.870 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: They got all butt
whoopings that everybody got.

00:37:43.870 --> 00:37:45.280 align:middle line:90%
They got all the yellings.

00:37:45.280 --> 00:37:46.622 align:middle line:90%
They got all the beatings.

00:37:46.622 --> 00:37:47.830 align:middle line:90%
They got all the punishments.

00:37:47.830 --> 00:37:50.110 align:middle line:90%
But that doesn't work.

00:37:50.110 --> 00:37:52.840 align:middle line:84%
You can't take children and
beat them, and yell at them,

00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:54.490 align:middle line:84%
and tell them all
kind of crazy stuff,

00:37:54.490 --> 00:37:56.200 align:middle line:90%
and expect them to be OK.

00:37:56.200 --> 00:37:58.833 align:middle line:84%
Only a small amount of kids
will make it out of that OK,

00:37:58.833 --> 00:38:00.250 align:middle line:84%
and the rest of
them will struggle

00:38:00.250 --> 00:38:01.417 align:middle line:90%
for the rest of their lives.

00:38:01.417 --> 00:38:02.950 align:middle line:84%
We're creating a
sick environment.

00:38:02.950 --> 00:38:05.847 align:middle line:84%
We're creating a sick race
of people of all skin colors

00:38:05.847 --> 00:38:07.930 align:middle line:84%
by doing this to them, and
treating them that way,

00:38:07.930 --> 00:38:09.513 align:middle line:84%
and beating them,
and yelling at them.

00:38:09.513 --> 00:38:11.270 align:middle line:90%
You can't do that.

00:38:11.270 --> 00:38:12.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:38:12.070 --> 00:38:14.860 align:middle line:90%


00:38:14.860 --> 00:38:21.337 align:middle line:10%
I don't know myself on this
level, but in modern times,

00:38:21.337 --> 00:38:23.170 align:middle line:10%
people look to the
African-American culture,

00:38:23.170 --> 00:38:25.628 align:middle line:10%
and they'll often say, well,
there wasn't a father present.

00:38:25.628 --> 00:38:26.580 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Right.

00:38:26.580 --> 00:38:28.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That
phenomena, which you've

00:38:28.450 --> 00:38:31.360 align:middle line:84%
reversed big time
in your genetics

00:38:31.360 --> 00:38:32.890 align:middle line:90%
and your lineage you were there.

00:38:32.890 --> 00:38:35.200 align:middle line:84%
Your dad was-- he was
screwed up, but he was there.

00:38:35.200 --> 00:38:36.117 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah, right.

00:38:36.117 --> 00:38:38.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He was there.

00:38:38.330 --> 00:38:42.820 align:middle line:10%
So what's happening right now--

00:38:42.820 --> 00:38:45.100 align:middle line:10%
tell us what's happening
in African-American culture

00:38:45.100 --> 00:38:46.210 align:middle line:10%
in that way.

00:38:46.210 --> 00:38:50.920 align:middle line:84%
Are the men starting to stay
or is the phenomena continuing?

00:38:50.920 --> 00:38:53.783 align:middle line:84%
And why has it
happened this way?

00:38:53.783 --> 00:38:56.200 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: I'll start by telling
you why it happened first.

00:38:56.200 --> 00:38:56.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:38:56.320 --> 00:38:57.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Because that's
the important part

00:38:57.340 --> 00:38:58.632 align:middle line:90%
that people need to understand.

00:38:58.632 --> 00:39:01.690 align:middle line:84%
When you look into the
history of, unfortunately,

00:39:01.690 --> 00:39:04.687 align:middle line:84%
racism on this planet, not just
even in the African-American

00:39:04.687 --> 00:39:05.770 align:middle line:90%
culture but all cultures--

00:39:05.770 --> 00:39:06.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, all racism.

00:39:06.410 --> 00:39:07.210 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:39:07.210 --> 00:39:14.230 align:middle line:84%
You begin to realize that the
way that we have been oppressed

00:39:14.230 --> 00:39:16.120 align:middle line:84%
and the way that
slavery occurred,

00:39:16.120 --> 00:39:19.810 align:middle line:84%
you were basically making
brother fight against brother

00:39:19.810 --> 00:39:24.370 align:middle line:84%
and also a lot of the raping,
and you're just a person

00:39:24.370 --> 00:39:26.410 align:middle line:90%
here to mate with these women--

00:39:26.410 --> 00:39:28.842 align:middle line:84%
you're like a buck so you
mate, mate, mate, mate, mate,

00:39:28.842 --> 00:39:30.050 align:middle line:90%
and then you're out of there.

00:39:30.050 --> 00:39:31.110 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
take these babies,

00:39:31.110 --> 00:39:32.318 align:middle line:90%
and we're going to sell them.

00:39:32.318 --> 00:39:34.030 align:middle line:90%
It's like a breeding plan.

00:39:34.030 --> 00:39:35.860 align:middle line:84%
Now what's important
to understand

00:39:35.860 --> 00:39:38.080 align:middle line:84%
is in your DNA-- your
DNA stores memories.

00:39:38.080 --> 00:39:39.330 align:middle line:90%
This is scientifically proven.

00:39:39.330 --> 00:39:40.413 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, absolutely.

00:39:40.413 --> 00:39:42.610 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: You also have
epigenetic memories.

00:39:42.610 --> 00:39:44.470 align:middle line:84%
These epigenetic
memories can persist

00:39:44.470 --> 00:39:45.860 align:middle line:90%
for 15 to 20 generations.

00:39:45.860 --> 00:39:46.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:46.660 --> 00:39:48.610 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: So what happened to--

00:39:48.610 --> 00:39:50.580 align:middle line:84%
if I had in any previous
people in my family

00:39:50.580 --> 00:39:53.222 align:middle line:84%
that were involved in
slavery, those memories, all

00:39:53.222 --> 00:39:55.180 align:middle line:84%
those tortures, and all
those mindsets, and all

00:39:55.180 --> 00:39:56.847 align:middle line:84%
those teachings, and
all those beatings,

00:39:56.847 --> 00:39:59.140 align:middle line:84%
and all that structure
that was put into them

00:39:59.140 --> 00:40:01.810 align:middle line:84%
back then is inside
of me as well.

00:40:01.810 --> 00:40:04.462 align:middle line:84%
Some of us have the capability
of reprogramming ourselves

00:40:04.462 --> 00:40:06.670 align:middle line:84%
a little bit easier than
others, but a lot of people,

00:40:06.670 --> 00:40:08.210 align:middle line:90%
they don't have the capability.

00:40:08.210 --> 00:40:10.630 align:middle line:84%
They're living out
past ancient memories

00:40:10.630 --> 00:40:14.722 align:middle line:84%
that have been taught and
bred into them in modern era.

00:40:14.722 --> 00:40:16.180 align:middle line:84%
So that's where
the problem starts.

00:40:16.180 --> 00:40:18.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The breaking
apart of the family

00:40:18.640 --> 00:40:20.365 align:middle line:84%
was the critical
basis for slavery.

00:40:20.365 --> 00:40:23.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Exactly, they
would take a woman,

00:40:23.050 --> 00:40:24.460 align:middle line:84%
and they would
take away the son.

00:40:24.460 --> 00:40:25.877 align:middle line:84%
He's going to go
up for sale here.

00:40:25.877 --> 00:40:27.220 align:middle line:90%
The daughter, she's a wench.

00:40:27.220 --> 00:40:30.040 align:middle line:84%
She's going off
for sale over here.

00:40:30.040 --> 00:40:32.230 align:middle line:84%
And she'll be raped,
and she'll have babies.

00:40:32.230 --> 00:40:34.090 align:middle line:84%
The guy, he's a buck
if he's strong enough.

00:40:34.090 --> 00:40:36.132 align:middle line:84%
He's going to mate with
all these different women

00:40:36.132 --> 00:40:39.700 align:middle line:84%
till they can have strong
babies that can go do the work.

00:40:39.700 --> 00:40:41.710 align:middle line:84%
It was bred in to
not be a father,

00:40:41.710 --> 00:40:44.085 align:middle line:84%
not be there for your children,
to just have sex and run.

00:40:44.085 --> 00:40:46.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're just being
used as a commodity yourself.

00:40:46.460 --> 00:40:47.500 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Exactly.

00:40:47.500 --> 00:40:50.733 align:middle line:84%
And people don't realize
that's in the genome.

00:40:50.733 --> 00:40:52.400 align:middle line:84%
And slavery just ended
not too long ago,

00:40:52.400 --> 00:40:54.430 align:middle line:84%
so it's going to persist
for quite a while.

00:40:54.430 --> 00:40:56.830 align:middle line:84%
So part of my mission
is to help reprogram

00:40:56.830 --> 00:40:59.650 align:middle line:84%
the mind of the
African-American, reprogram

00:40:59.650 --> 00:41:01.150 align:middle line:84%
the way that we
think about things.

00:41:01.150 --> 00:41:03.447 align:middle line:84%
So to help us heal
ourselves, we've

00:41:03.447 --> 00:41:04.780 align:middle line:90%
got to heal from the inside out.

00:41:04.780 --> 00:41:05.835 align:middle line:90%
And it's getting better.

00:41:05.835 --> 00:41:07.210 align:middle line:84%
When I went to
Brooklyn, New York

00:41:07.210 --> 00:41:12.100 align:middle line:84%
to do my lecture two weeks ago,
there were 500 people there

00:41:12.100 --> 00:41:15.140 align:middle line:90%
at that St. Francis College.

00:41:15.140 --> 00:41:18.400 align:middle line:84%
I think there we might have
been five other races there.

00:41:18.400 --> 00:41:20.110 align:middle line:84%
But to see that
many people coming

00:41:20.110 --> 00:41:22.280 align:middle line:84%
for this kind of
information, it blew me away.

00:41:22.280 --> 00:41:23.080 align:middle line:90%
I was shocked.

00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:25.210 align:middle line:84%
When I walked in the
room, I go, whoa.

00:41:25.210 --> 00:41:26.030 align:middle line:90%
That's incredible.

00:41:26.030 --> 00:41:28.350 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea that
was going to happen.

00:41:28.350 --> 00:41:30.970 align:middle line:84%
And these people were really
into this kind of information--

00:41:30.970 --> 00:41:32.950 align:middle line:84%
alternative thinking,
away from religion,

00:41:32.950 --> 00:41:35.740 align:middle line:84%
more into spirituality,
unconditional love,

00:41:35.740 --> 00:41:36.550 align:middle line:90%
all these things.

00:41:36.550 --> 00:41:39.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the
communities of black people now

00:41:39.130 --> 00:41:42.520 align:middle line:84%
around the world, especially
in America in particular,

00:41:42.520 --> 00:41:44.960 align:middle line:84%
has been changing and
going for the better.

00:41:44.960 --> 00:41:47.410 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot more
fathers at home

00:41:47.410 --> 00:41:50.360 align:middle line:84%
now, a lot more fathers
taking care of their kids.

00:41:50.360 --> 00:41:51.390 align:middle line:90%
It's getting better.

00:41:51.390 --> 00:41:52.598 align:middle line:90%
They're getting a lot better.

00:41:52.598 --> 00:41:56.595 align:middle line:90%


00:41:56.595 --> 00:41:59.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like you
say, it's still so raw.

00:41:59.910 --> 00:42:01.230 align:middle line:90%
It's fresh.

00:42:01.230 --> 00:42:04.650 align:middle line:10%
It's only so many generations
ago, not that many.

00:42:04.650 --> 00:42:06.960 align:middle line:10%
And the repercussions
of it and the prejudice

00:42:06.960 --> 00:42:09.360 align:middle line:10%
that has continued
since then has barely

00:42:09.360 --> 00:42:12.540 align:middle line:10%
waned in some parts of even
the United States, certainly

00:42:12.540 --> 00:42:14.340 align:middle line:10%
the United States.

00:42:14.340 --> 00:42:19.020 align:middle line:10%
It seems to have taken more of a
backseat in Britain and Europe,

00:42:19.020 --> 00:42:21.690 align:middle line:10%
at least for
African-Americans anyway--

00:42:21.690 --> 00:42:24.760 align:middle line:10%
for blacks than it has
for African-Americans.

00:42:24.760 --> 00:42:27.053 align:middle line:84%
America seems to be a really
tough culture in this way.

00:42:27.053 --> 00:42:28.470 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: It's
pretty tough, yeah.

00:42:28.470 --> 00:42:31.877 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: you know, I had
a conversation with Raymond

00:42:31.877 --> 00:42:33.960 align:middle line:84%
Tarpey, and he and I had
been talking on the phone

00:42:33.960 --> 00:42:35.030 align:middle line:90%
beforehand.

00:42:35.030 --> 00:42:36.720 align:middle line:84%
And it was a really
interesting thing

00:42:36.720 --> 00:42:38.580 align:middle line:84%
he brought up that we
did not get into when

00:42:38.580 --> 00:42:40.510 align:middle line:90%
the interview came around.

00:42:40.510 --> 00:42:48.880 align:middle line:84%
He said that America's
immaturity and entitlement

00:42:48.880 --> 00:42:52.810 align:middle line:84%
is, in part, to do with the
fact that this country never

00:42:52.810 --> 00:42:57.940 align:middle line:84%
had to actually pay up and
reconcile with slavery, where

00:42:57.940 --> 00:43:01.960 align:middle line:84%
in other countries there was
some kind of reconciliation,

00:43:01.960 --> 00:43:03.055 align:middle line:90%
compensation, something.

00:43:03.055 --> 00:43:03.670 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Right.

00:43:03.670 --> 00:43:05.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it
never happened here.

00:43:05.230 --> 00:43:06.715 align:middle line:10%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:43:06.715 --> 00:43:09.760 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: In your
mind, how can that

00:43:09.760 --> 00:43:13.102 align:middle line:10%
be healed when the country
never took responsibility

00:43:13.102 --> 00:43:13.935 align:middle line:10%
for what we've done?

00:43:13.935 --> 00:43:16.352 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: They keep saying,
oh, that happened in the past,

00:43:16.352 --> 00:43:18.770 align:middle line:84%
and that was our ancestors
or our relatives or whatever,

00:43:18.770 --> 00:43:19.570 align:middle line:90%
but it wasn't us.

00:43:19.570 --> 00:43:23.020 align:middle line:84%
But again, science needs
to come to the forefront

00:43:23.020 --> 00:43:26.050 align:middle line:84%
now and explain the
suffering that's going on.

00:43:26.050 --> 00:43:27.820 align:middle line:84%
People are suffering
from PTSD from things

00:43:27.820 --> 00:43:29.140 align:middle line:90%
that happened 200 years ago.

00:43:29.140 --> 00:43:30.715 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:43:30.715 --> 00:43:32.500 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't
agree with you more.

00:43:32.500 --> 00:43:35.240 align:middle line:84%
This is where science
and spirituality actually

00:43:35.240 --> 00:43:36.490 align:middle line:90%
need to come forward together.

00:43:36.490 --> 00:43:37.600 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yes, I agree.

00:43:37.600 --> 00:43:38.200 align:middle line:90%
I agree 100%.

00:43:38.200 --> 00:43:39.658 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So when
you do your talks

00:43:39.658 --> 00:43:42.190 align:middle line:84%
to these groups
of people, do you

00:43:42.190 --> 00:43:44.125 align:middle line:84%
approach it from a
genetic standpoint

00:43:44.125 --> 00:43:45.250 align:middle line:90%
and a spiritual standpoint?

00:43:45.250 --> 00:43:45.820 align:middle line:90%
>>CARSON: Yeah.

00:43:45.820 --> 00:43:46.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What do you do?

00:43:46.320 --> 00:43:46.880 align:middle line:90%
What's your story?

00:43:46.880 --> 00:43:49.385 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: A lot of my lectures
are very scientific because I

00:43:49.385 --> 00:43:51.010 align:middle line:84%
like to show people
the spiritual side,

00:43:51.010 --> 00:43:52.480 align:middle line:84%
but I like the show
them-- before I

00:43:52.480 --> 00:43:54.910 align:middle line:84%
get to the spiritual
aspect, I show them science.

00:43:54.910 --> 00:43:56.170 align:middle line:90%
So they can say, oh, wow.

00:43:56.170 --> 00:43:57.170 align:middle line:90%
This is really possible.

00:43:57.170 --> 00:43:59.002 align:middle line:84%
These two things really
do work together.

00:43:59.002 --> 00:44:00.460 align:middle line:84%
Because people tend
to think things

00:44:00.460 --> 00:44:05.050 align:middle line:84%
in spirituality and spiritual
concepts are more like "magic"

00:44:05.050 --> 00:44:07.925 align:middle line:84%
and some kind of way
things are just happening,

00:44:07.925 --> 00:44:09.800 align:middle line:84%
but I like to show them
why they're happening

00:44:09.800 --> 00:44:10.800 align:middle line:90%
and how their happening.

00:44:10.800 --> 00:44:13.038 align:middle line:84%
This is the science
behind why this works

00:44:13.038 --> 00:44:14.830 align:middle line:84%
and why these kind of
thought process work,

00:44:14.830 --> 00:44:16.750 align:middle line:84%
why these kind of
meditations work.

00:44:16.750 --> 00:44:19.240 align:middle line:84%
And then they begin to go,
wow, this is incredible.

00:44:19.240 --> 00:44:22.210 align:middle line:84%
Now they're going,
I see, and, I want

00:44:22.210 --> 00:44:25.150 align:middle line:84%
to follow this path
instead of the other path.

00:44:25.150 --> 00:44:27.130 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, religion
really held us down

00:44:27.130 --> 00:44:28.090 align:middle line:90%
a lot more as well.

00:44:28.090 --> 00:44:29.470 align:middle line:84%
That's another big
thing that happened.

00:44:29.470 --> 00:44:30.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:44:30.280 --> 00:44:32.613 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: People tend to think
that religions got spread

00:44:32.613 --> 00:44:34.600 align:middle line:84%
around the planet by
love, but it really

00:44:34.600 --> 00:44:38.740 align:middle line:84%
got spread around the planet by
force, by rape, and by murder,

00:44:38.740 --> 00:44:39.730 align:middle line:90%
unfortunately.

00:44:39.730 --> 00:44:40.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, absolutely.

00:44:40.960 --> 00:44:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And if you're in America, God's
a white guy with a white beard.

00:44:44.370 --> 00:44:45.940 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: Right,
with a magic wand.

00:44:45.940 --> 00:44:46.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:44:46.740 --> 00:44:51.700 align:middle line:84%
>>CARSON: And it robs
you of your identity.

00:44:51.700 --> 00:44:53.740 align:middle line:84%
Almost every race
has an identity

00:44:53.740 --> 00:44:55.840 align:middle line:90%
that they can correlate with.

00:44:55.840 --> 00:44:59.620 align:middle line:84%
But in America, we're
called African-Americans,

00:44:59.620 --> 00:45:03.935 align:middle line:84%
but there's not Asian-Americans
or Caucasian-Americans.

00:45:03.935 --> 00:45:05.560 align:middle line:84%
So we've lost-- we've
been disconnected

00:45:05.560 --> 00:45:08.650 align:middle line:84%
from our roots, disconnected
from the alchemical sciences

00:45:08.650 --> 00:45:10.150 align:middle line:90%
that we used to know.

00:45:10.150 --> 00:45:13.120 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, when we
got into the religious aspect

00:45:13.120 --> 00:45:16.120 align:middle line:84%
of things, we were only
given small amounts

00:45:16.120 --> 00:45:21.380 align:middle line:84%
of verses that would approve
slavery and slave tactics.

00:45:21.380 --> 00:45:23.580 align:middle line:84%
And that has still
been embedded in us

00:45:23.580 --> 00:45:25.870 align:middle line:84%
till this very day in
the religious aspects.

00:45:25.870 --> 00:45:29.140 align:middle line:84%
So people have gotten
used to that system,

00:45:29.140 --> 00:45:30.915 align:middle line:84%
and some people actually
rejoice and think

00:45:30.915 --> 00:45:32.290 align:middle line:84%
that all those
millions of people

00:45:32.290 --> 00:45:35.215 align:middle line:84%
had to die just so that they
can learn what's in that book.

00:45:35.215 --> 00:45:36.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A lot of
this was exemplified

00:45:36.970 --> 00:45:40.120 align:middle line:84%
in a film called
"Harriet," which is out,

00:45:40.120 --> 00:45:43.000 align:middle line:84%
a character, a heroine
of her day, a slave who

00:45:43.000 --> 00:45:45.500 align:middle line:84%
broke away and started becoming
a part of the Underground

00:45:45.500 --> 00:45:46.300 align:middle line:90%
Railroad.

